profile_positions.description:
Defined the Sustainable Procurement strategy and goals for ING in the Netherlands. Leading and managing the key strategic pillars:

1. Supplier Sustainability Assessment Program 
- monitor the supplier sustainability performance using EcoVadis;
- provide consultancy and support to suppliers to improve key ESG topics based on material issues;
- monitor and report on program's performance across the Netherlands;

2. Sustainable Purchasing Decisions 
- design and lead the integration of ESG questions/criteria in relevant purchasing projects;
- subject matter expertise: prove assessment on supplier ESG performance as part of the decision making process;
- working with internal stakeholders to address and improve key issues within our own operations (advance the circular economy uptake, lower our footprint, etc)

3. Supplier Sustainability Management System
- internal policy development to support the ING's sustainable procurement program 
- communication (internally and externally) around the program objectives and results
- ensuring alignment with EU / NL legislation concerning ESG topics in supply chains
- area specific contribution to relevant certifications like ISO certifications, CDP submissions, etc

1. Project Management - leading pan-European projects and partnerships that focus on delivering practical entrepreneurial experiences to students aged 15-18 years old. Main responsibilities:
- strengthening relationships with top donors (account management for companies like UBS, Barclays, SAP, Microsoft, Citi Foundation, FedEx);
- coordinating the network of national project managers to ensure timely delivery of the pan-European projects;
- designing education materials, marketing materials and coordinating communication efforts around the partnerships;
- developing educational platforms with the help of external providers;

2. Network management & Project management of EU-funded project - managing an EU-funded network of 50 entrepreneurship education experts from Europe (http://www.ee-hub.eu/) that aims to increase the uptake of entrepreneurship education in the Member States national education strategy and European schools:
- event management - online and face to face events;
- communication with the network and European Commission;
- marketing activities;
- reporting and financial control over the project.

3. Fundraising - contributing to grant proposals, pitch preparation, reporting and evaluations for the corporate donors.

1. Responsible for ensuring sustainable operations of the national headquarters:
- managed the national finance team;
- managed the national budget (74,000+ €) and the legal, administrative daily processes;
- strategic planning and consulting for the financial department of 15 local chapters;
- planned and implemented a financial education program for members of the department;
- applied for EU grants and managed the implementation of a 50,000€ EU-funded project
- legal transition of the management of the organisation

2. Project & event management - designed and managed the agenda of a national event, Romania Youth Leadership Forum 2010 (500 attendees, 230 alumni, 30 partner companies, 15 trainers, 40,000€ profit).
